                    <h3>Investment Planning</h3> <hr> <br>
                    <p style="padding: 50px;">Investment planning is the process of creating a strategy to manage and grow your financial resources over time. It involves setting specific financial goals, assessing your risk tolerance, and making informed decisions about how to allocate your money among different investment options. Here are some key steps in investment planning:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ul style="text-align: left;">
                            <li>Define Your Goals: Clearly identify your financial objectives, such as saving for retirement, buying a home, or funding your children's education.
                            </li>
                            <li>Assess Risk Tolerance: Understand how much risk you are willing and able to take with your investments. 
                                This will help determine your asset allocation.</li>
                                <li>Asset Allocation: Diversify your investments across different asset classes, such as stocks, bonds, real estate, and cash, based on your risk tolerance and goals.
                                </li>
                                <li> Investment Selection: Choose specific investments that align with your asset allocation, such as individual stocks, mutual funds, exchange-traded funds (ETFs), or other financial instruments.
                                </li>
                                <li>Monitor and Rebalance: Regularly review your portfolio to ensure it remains in line with your goals and risk tolerance. Rebalance if necessary.
                                </li>
                                <li>Long-Term Perspective: Understand that investing is a long-term endeavor. Avoid making impulsive decisions based on short-term market fluctuations.
                                </li>
                                <li> Seek Professional Advice: Consider consulting a financial advisor to help you create a customized investment plan.
                                </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
